X.

May 3, 1910.

Hon. Lyman Beecher Stowe,
55 Washington Square,
New York City.

Dear Sir:

In the absence of President Gompers on official business,
I beg to acknowledge receipt of your favor of May 2d, which will
be brought to his attention immediately upon his return to headquarters.

Very truly yours,

Secretary to
